@TKOG13: It is good to learn, even if its technically impossible to say for ALL handhelds, even for majority of iPods. CABAC is used as entropy model, and by the book - iPod doesn't accept this. On contrary, PSP "hates" CAVLC (accepted by iPods) and "love" CABAC.
Also - sound. By the numbers no habdheld should accept   AAC LC-SBR-PS (AAC Low Complexity with Spectral Band Replication and Parametric Stereo) but strictly AAC LS with 44.1 kHz sampling rate (here is 22,05).
Therefore, [quark]s are completely without iTunes bits/info (UUID needed  by older firmwares).
So, feel lucky - 'cause - believe it or not - some people have problems with my all other encodings - which are... 110% compatible.

@Jon: Thank you, my friend.

@TKOG13: Sorry, a dawn "blindness":

AAC LS = AAC LC

habdheld = handheld (LOL)
